The paper deals with information theory and communication protocols for distributed source coding, which are topics covered in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of block-coding, which is a topic covered in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel information measure and investigates the role of worst-case analysis, which are topics covered in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories, respectively.
